wiki.content: “Over You” sees Australian rapper and singer The Kid LAROI hurt after a past relationship. He details his hopelessness, desperation for support, and negative attitude to his former partners over a melodic instrumental with high-flying harmonies. The song was originally expected on LAROI’s July 2020 mixtape, F*CK LOVE, but many were surprised to see its absence from the final tracklist. It was soon after played in its entirety during an Instagram Live conducted by Khaled Rohaim, one of the track’s producers, and the same version later released on F*CK LOVE 3: OVER YOU.
